22
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Bêguman jiyana gundan pir xweş e.
 
Without a doubt, village life is very beautiful.

23
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:23,000
Berî em derbasî gundê Tirmîşa dibin, silav û hurmet ji we
re, silav û rêz ji we re.
 
Before we enter the village of Tirmisha, greetings and
respect to you, greetings and regards to you.

24
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Ez dixwazim amadebûna silav bikim, û amadebûnên li ber dilê
min biha ye.
 
I want to greet the attendees, and the attendees are dear to
my heart.

25
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Mala Mihemed Nûr ji gundê Tirmîşa ne, niha li bazara Efrînê
dimînin.
 
Mihemed Nur's family is from Tirmisha village, they
currently live in the Afrin market.

26
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Xwediyê Kafê Muhîto, silav û hurmet ji wan malbatê tevayî
re, silavê me ji wan re hene.
 
The owner of Cafe Mojito, greetings and respect to that
entire family, we send them our greetings.

27
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Niha jî em herin em ê derbas gundê Tirmîşa bin.
 
Now let's go, we will enter the village of Tirmisha.

28
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Belê temaşevanên me yê hêja, niha jî em derbasî gundê
Tirmîşa bûn.
 
Yes our dear viewers, now we have entered the village of
Tirmisha.

29
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:32,000
Maşallah gundê Tirmîşa pir gundekî xweş e. Li bilindiyê
dikeve.
 
Mashallah, the village of Tirmisha is a very beautiful
village. It is located on a height.

30
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Ew jî navçeya Şiyê ye.
 
And it belongs to the Shiye district.

31
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Niha em ê bi hevra derbasî nav gund bin, hin cihan xweş ji
gund biweşînin.
 
Now we will enter the village together, and broadcast some
beautiful places from the village.

32
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Û em ê sekne em ê derbas cem kêjan dayîkê bin, û çi xwarinên
Efrînî wê ji me re çêke.
 
And we will see which mother we will visit, and what Afrin
food she will make for us.

33
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:53,000
Belê temaşevanên me yê hêja, niha jî em li gundê Tirmîşa
derbasî malbatekê bûn.
 
Yes our dear viewers, now we have entered a family's home in
Tirmisha village.

34
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,000
Vê malbatê jê re dibêjin Alî Hesenî Gulîn.
 
This family is called Ali Heseni Gulin.

35
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Em bi vê dayîka xwe re rûniştin e, dayîkek ji dayîkên me yên
Efrînî.
 
We sat down with this mother of ours, a mother from our
Afrin mothers.

36
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:06,000
Ez û mamoste Xelîl, dê pirsan ji vê dayîkê ra bikin, em ê
jiyanê wê nas bikin.
 
Teacher Xelil and I will ask this mother questions, we will
get to know her life.

37
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Es-selamû eleykum dayê.
 
Peace be upon you, mother.

38
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Eleykum selam qurbanî.
 
Peace be upon you too, my sacrifice.

39
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Tu çawa yî?
 
How are you?

40
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Elhemdulelah.
 
Praise be to God.

41
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,000
Em te nas bikin berî her tiştî.
 
Let's get to know you before anything else.

42
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,000
Ehl û sehlan.
 
Welcome.

43
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Navê te bi xêr?
 
Your good name?

44
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Xedîce ye.
 
It's Xedice.

45
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Ebbos, navê gundî...
 
Xedice...

46
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Ebbos, navê gundî...
 
Ebbos, the village name...

47
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Tu bi canê xwe xweş e, tu kêfsiz e?
 
Are you physically well, are you unwell?

48
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Wele elhemdulelah.
 
Well, praise be to God.

49
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,000
Elhemdulelah, şukir ji Xwedê re.
 
Praise be to God, thanks to God.

50
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:27,000
Maşelleh emrê te jî bereket heye yanî...
 
Mashallah, your age is blessed too, meaning...

51
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Bes e wele.
 
It's enough, by God.

52
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Elhemdulelah şukir.
 
Praise be to God, thanks.

53
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Wekî dema berê da çawa bû siheta te, çawa bû?
 
How was your health in the past, how was it?

54
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Wele sihet... berê baştir bû. Niha emr diçe, êdî emî derbaz
kirin.
 
Well, health... was better before. Now age is advancing, we
have passed it.

55
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Elhemdulelah şukir ji Xwedê re.
 
Praise be to God, thanks to God.

56
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,000
Ez dizanim...
 
I know...

57
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:49,000
Keça min, şekir e, şuhûm e, kirîstan e, ev tişt, kerratî ye,
nizanim çi ye...
 
My daughter, it's diabetes, cholesterol, crystals, these
things, deafness, I don't know what...

58
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Elhemdulelah şukir ji Xwedê re...
 
Praise be to God, thanks to God...

59
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
Hemdullah hemdullah.
 
Praise be, praise be.

60
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,000
Xwedê sihetek xweş bide te xaltî.
 
May God give you good health, aunt.

61
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Pîrekê haziyan nayê, dibêjin emrê şêstî, xercê sekînî.
 
The elders say, at the age of sixty, you're worn out.

62
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Em bi ser şêstî ketine.
 
We have passed sixty.

63
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Ji şêstî ketiye?
 
You passed sixty?

64
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Hê ji mêj ve ketine.
 
We passed it a long time ago.

65
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Xwedê emrekî dirêj bide we, dest bi sihetekê bike.
 
May God give you a long life, with good health.

66
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Bes elhemdulelah şukir ji Xwedê re.
 
But praise be to God, thanks to God.

67
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Xaltî em îro pir kêfxweş bûn ku em hatin gundê te, derbasî
gundê Tirmîşa bûn, ev cara yekê em tên.
 
Aunt, we are very happy today that we came to your village,
entered Tirmisha village, this is our first time coming.

68
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Ehl û sehlan.
 
Welcome.

69
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Go em bi dayîkan re jî rûniştin, em daxwazin îca me re
xeberek bidin ser heyata xwe, wehda xwe.
 
When we sat down with the mothers, we wanted you to tell us
a bit about your life, your time.

70
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:22,000
Wele dayê heyata me me çêbî, me gund derbas kirin. Ne...
rind xirab me gund derbas kir, me dûr jî dît, me nêzîk jî
dît.
 
Well mother, our life happened, we passed through the
village. Not... good or bad, we passed through the village,
we saw far and we saw near.

71
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

72
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Elhemdulelah, dîsa elhemdulelah.
 
Praise be to God, again praise be to God.

73
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,000
Elhemdulelah şukir ji Xwedê re.
 
Praise be to God, thanks to God.

74
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,000
Ji Xwedê re şukir...
 
Thanks to God...

75
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,000
Jiyana gund û kêfa gund û dinyayê...
 
Village life and the joy of the village and the world...

76
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:41,000
Me ev saetên dirêj dikişandin, niha jî tînin, me nan jî
dikir, hevrîşk jî distiran, me nan jî dikir, me kinc jî
dişûştin bi avê ji bîr û deran didan, me dişûştin... Û dîsa
em ji nû ve pê ketine. Elhemdulelah şukir, kefte dinya ye,
elhemdulelah.
 
We used to pull those long hours, even now we do, we baked
bread, we kneaded dough, we baked bread, we washed clothes
with water drawn from wells and outside, we washed them...
And again we started over. Praise be to God, thanks, the
world has fallen into place, praise be to God.

77
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:44,000
Berê derd kul tunebûn, tişt... şewat tunebûn, qehir tunebû,
niha êdî tişt...
 
Before there was no pain or sorrow, things... no burning, no
anger, now things are...

78
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Dîsa elhemdulelah.
 
Again praise be to God.

79
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Ev tiştên ku te behs dikirin xaltîk, rastiye, raste tu
dibêje we berê pir dikişand... lê ewan...
 
The things you mentioned aunt, it's true, it's true you say
you used to pull a lot... but those...

80
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Xweş bû.
 
It was nice.

81
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Xweş bû.
 
It was nice.

82
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Xweş bû, jiyaneke xweş bû. Erê.
 
It was nice, it was a nice life. Yes.

83
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Haskirin zêde bû.
 
There was more love.

84
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,000
Ji gîda xweş bû, emaniya da, sîqeta da.
 
It was nice from all sides, in trust, in reliability.

85
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

86
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Ji gîda xweş bû, emaniya de, ji xweşbûnê û sîqetê de jî xweş
bû. Ji gîda xweş bû qurban. Ne wekî nûka bû.
 
It was nice from all sides, in trust, in happiness and
reliability it was nice. It was nice from all sides, my
sacrifice. It wasn't like now.

87
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

88
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Nûka wekî nûka bû, na...
 
Now, it was like now, no...

89
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,000
We te çend zarok mezin kirin e?
 
How many children did you raise?

90
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:13,000
Heft qîz û dudu law.
 
Seven girls and two boys.

91
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:17,000
Û elhemdulelah nûka ji wan bitenê mane.
 
And praise be to God, now they are left alone.

92
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,000
Elhemdulelah.
 
Praise be to God.

93
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,000
Xwedê wan staro ke.
 
May God protect them.

94
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:29,000
Qîzek yek rehmetî bû, dudu law mane... Çar qîçik mane, yek
jî wefa da... Kule me jî rehmetî bûn, iştê... Êdî wilo, bes
yek qîzek yek li cem min e.
 
One girl passed away, two boys are left... Four little girls
are left, one passed away... Our loved ones also passed
away, well... That's how it is, just one girl is with me.

95
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Xwedê hiştê de be.
 
May God keep her for you.

96
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Navê vê zehterê ewê çi lê ne xaltî?
 
What do they call this thyme, aunt?

97
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Jê re dibêjin çolê ye vira. Ev çolê ye...
 
They call it wild here. This is wild...

98
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,000
Ev zeterê eslî ye.
 
This is the original thyme.

99
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,000
Ev a eslî ye.
 
This is the original one.

100
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Berê ku çû zani bû bê gîha eslî ne an ne eslî ye.
 
Back then, how did they know if the herb was original or
not?

101
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:53,000
Ew a çîçeka vî... ev gîhayê çîçeka vî mohrikan êdî, doxa vî
biharê çend roja din e nuha, ewa kulîlkê xwe vedikin...
mohrikan ê... êdî nevane.
 
The flower of this... this flower herb has beads, its time
is in spring, in a few days now, it will open its flowers...
beads... it's not like that anymore.

102
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Û hûn ê çê dî wê derê dikin li vê çolê xaltî?
 
And what else do you do out there in this wild, aunt?

103
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Erê li çolê ha, li derî vira ye.
 
Yes, in the wild here, outside here.

104
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Ev xwarinek Efrînî ev a me çêkir.
 
This is an Afrin food we made.

105
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:03,000
Ê Efrînî ye, tiştê din e. Erê.
 
Yes, it's Afrin style, it's something else. Yes.

106
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:06,000
Ev xwarina Efrînî... ez zanim bes li Efrînê çêdibin e.
 
This Afrin food... I know it is only made in Afrin.

107
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,000
Erê Efrîn çêdikin, erê.
 
Yes, they make it in Afrin, yes.

108
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Ê tiştên ser obekatin e...
 
And the things that go on top...

109
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:16,000
Zater û zeytûn e û divê me stey kiriye...
 
Thyme and olives and we have to put it...

110
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:22,000
Erê... zater e... zeytûn e... salata zaterê tê re.
 
Yes... it's thyme... it's olives... thyme salad goes with
it.

111
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

112
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Te penîr jê çêkir e, penîr te nekiriye tê?
 
Did you make cheese out of it, didn't you put cheese in it?

113
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,000
Na penêr nakinê.
 
No, they don't put cheese.

114
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:31,000
Penîr dikin e.
 
They do put cheese.

115
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:40,000
Penîr dixeve, zeytûn dixeve... bîber e, sîr e... iştê ev
tişt tê de dikeve.
 
Cheese goes in, olives go in... pepper, garlic... well,
these things go into it.

116
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Ev jî nehne ye.
 
This is mint too.

117
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,000
Heta vê nehnana xaltîk, we bi destê xwe çêkirin e.
 
Even this mint, aunt, you made it with your own hands.

118
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:02,000
Lê nanê xwa jî, em bi destê xwe hişkî dikişînin ê. Û isod
e...
 
Yes, our own bread, we pull the dough with our own hands.
And it's pepper...

119
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,000
Ma we qey sîr jî...
 
Did you even put garlic...

120
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
Erê dî.
 
Yes indeed.

121
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:10,000
Û penîr xaltî hûn dikirin, lê dîsa hûn bi destê xwe çêdikin
e?
 
And cheese aunt, did you buy it, or do you make it with your
own hands again?

122
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:21,000
Wele ewro î pezê xwe ye, ez bi destê xwe çêdikira, û ev pezê
min tuneye dikirim.
 
Well, today, it's our own sheep, I used to make it with my
own hands, but now I don't have sheep so I buy it.

123
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:28,000
Me nanik yanî mi jê dikir, me qet... qet me jê dikir zêyt û
şekir... me li ser selê xweş dikir...
 
We used to make small breads from it, we never... we always
made it with oil and sugar... we baked it nicely on the sadj
(griddle)...

124
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

125
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,000
Kumba... berê da kumba jê...
 
Kumba... in the past, kumba...

126
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:36,000
Welle ewro kumba dikirin... min xwa bi serî nedikir.
 
Well today they made kumba... I didn't do it myself.

127
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,000
Kinafe...
 
Kunafa...

128
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:40,000
Nê... ew e tiştî na...
 
No... that thing, no...

129
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:58,000
Serî li xelkê dikir arê...
 
I made it for others, yes...

130
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:03,000
Ez zanim ev selata behîvê hişk jî dikevinê. We... we behîv
diketê ne?
 
I know this salad also includes dried almonds. Did... did
you put almonds in it?

131
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:06,000
Beîv tê kevine... gûz di tê kevin...
 
Almonds go in... walnuts go in...

132
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:09,000
Na nê gûza teye xaltîk... tiştî gûza adîye?
 
No, not your walnuts aunt... is it just regular walnuts?

133
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:17,000
Erê dibên temtê kek... Erê erê... awa selete... erê.
 
Yes, they say it's like cake... Yes, yes... that's the
salad... yes.

134
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:22,000
Yê xayero dikê yê gî dikê yê çi tiştî...
 
Some put cucumbers, some put all sorts, some put whatever...

135
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:29,000
Erê çê... Eslî...
 
Yes, it's good... Original...

136
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:32,000
Ev qîzika teye yê ha...
 
Is this your daughter here...

137
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,000
Keça min!
 
My daughter!

138
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,000
Xaltîk!
 
Aunt!

139
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:39,000
Qîza min! Tu tiştek nagihîje kezebê.
 
My daughter! Nothing compares to a child.

140
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:42,000
Xaltîka min, tiştek ji kezebê şêrîntir nîne.
 
My aunt, there is nothing sweeter than a child.

141
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Nuko seke... me hestiyê xwe canê xwe da ser kezebê. Sal nebû
ka qîza min rehmetî bû, sal nebû ka kurê min rehmetî bû...
 
Now look... we sacrificed our bones and our soul for our
children. A year hasn't passed since my daughter died, a
year hasn't passed since my son died...

142
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,000
Xwedê rehma xwe lê bike.
 
May God have mercy on them.

143
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:56,000
Tiştek ji kezebê şêrîntir nîne. Xwedê te sabir bike...
 
There is nothing sweeter than a child. May God give you
patience...

144
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,000
Dibêjin kokilîkê kela.
 
They say it's like a boiling pot.

145
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Dibêjin ew kokilîkê kela...
 
They say it's like a boiling pot...

146
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,000
Îcar ez ji te re nebêjim.
 
Now, what can I say to you.

147
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:06,000
Qet medî. Ev çi ye?
 
I haven't seen it at all. What is this?

148
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Ev seleteya zehter e.
 
This is a za'atar salad.

149
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Ev seleteya zehter e.
 
This is a za'atar salad.

150
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,000
Erê zehter e.
 
Yes, it is za'atar.

151
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:19,000
Saeta te xweş xaltîk, destên te sax bin. Xaltîkê berî...
 
Bless your time auntie, bless your hands. Auntie, before...

152
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:35,000
Qurbana te bim. Penêr, zehter, sîr, û dims û zeytûn û zeyt û
xeyar û bîber.
 
May I be your sacrifice. Cheese, za'atar, garlic, and
molasses, and olives, and oil, and cucumbers, and peppers.

153
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Destên te sax bin xaltîk.
 
Bless your hands auntie.

154
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:41,000
Saet xweş yavrum, qurban.
 
Bless your time my child, may I be your sacrifice.

155
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:48,000
Saet xweş xaltîk. Ez dixwazim te ji me re hinekî berê de,
Xwedê jê razî be... şîretek çêdikir.
 
Bless your time auntie. I want you to tell us a bit about
the past, may God be pleased with him... they used to give
advice.

156
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:54,000
Çi şîretan dikirin? Heta em gihîştin vê umrê, em li ser wê
şîretê mezin bûn.
 
What kind of advice did they give? Until we reached this
age, we grew up on that advice.

157
00:10:54,000 --> 00:11:00,000
Çi tişt Xwedê te dikir, heta naha di aqlê te da ye?
 
What did God make you do, that is still in your mind today?

158
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:06,000
Ê velleh yavrum, hin di aqlê me de dimîne û hin jî namîne.
 
Well by God my child, some remains in our mind and some does
not.

159
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:14,000
Xwedê niha... me digot firra mekin... yanî fesadiya mekin...
şîret... yanî boxtana xelkê mekin... we tiştên ne di cî da
ne...
 
Now by God... they told us not to talk behind people's
backs... meaning don't cause mischief... advice... meaning
don't slander people... those things that are out of
place...

160
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:18,000
Me nedîtin û sond nexwin... keda we di ye, mal qetil û mal
xirabî nekin.
 
"Don't swear about what you haven't seen... your labor is
seen, don't murder a family or ruin a household."

161
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:25,000
Digot yavrum, sond nexwin, sondxwarin xirab e. Bes ku...
eger biyaniyek be... qetil pêve ye, mal xirabî pêve ye.
 
They used to say my child, don't swear, swearing is bad.
Only if... if it's a stranger... murder is tied to it,
ruining a home is tied to it.

162
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:28,000
Digot cîhê we ne li vê derê ye, ne li wê derê ye.
 
They used to say your place is neither here nor there.

163
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:30,000
Sitare bikin yanî?
 
Meaning to cover it up (protect)?

164
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:38,000
Sitare... Erê lê sitara we nû kiye. Nêre min şîret lê nedî,
min tiştek nedî, ez nizanim. Ez nedî me û ez nizanim.
 
Cover it up... Yes, but your cover-up is new. Look, I didn't
see advice in it, I didn't see anything, I don't know. I
haven't seen and I don't know.

165
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:46,000
Sitare ji rebbê jor da ye. Xêr dibêjin sitare, sitara fatîma
nebî ye. Xêr we şîretek dikirin.
 
Cover-up is from the Lord above. Goodness they say is a
cover-up, the cover-up of Fatima the prophet. Goodness, they
gave such advice.

166
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:52,000
Ê de îştek yavrum... de naha jî ew nînin.
 
Well there you go my child... well they aren't around
anymore either.

167
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:55,000
Çûçik e... çawa filitîn e.
 
They are like birds... how they have flown away.

168
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:58,000
Ne çûçik e qurban, pir fit in.
 
They aren't birds my sacrifice, they are very cunning.

169
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Ê de îştek... xelkê lê naxele, wan wekî berê qurban...
 
Well there you go... the people can't be fooled, they aren't
like before my sacrifice...

170
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:04,000
Digot heta şîreta xwesiya we ye, ya qelfetiya we ye...
 
They said even the advice of your mother-in-law, or your
daughter-in-law...

171
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:06,000
Heta da û xwesiya...
 
Even mother and mother-in-law...

172
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:12,000
Û kalikê, û gitiyê xanê... giştî ne... Digot bîst salê
qaşmer a malê ye...
 
And the grandfather, and the elders of the house... all of
them... They used to say for twenty years she is the fool of
the house...

173
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:15,000
Heta salekê qaşmer a malê.
 
Up to a year, the fool of the house.

174
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,000
Heta salekê qaşmer...
 
A fool for up to a year...

175
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,000
Heta ku hîn bibe.
 
Until she learns.

176
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:24,000
Noka heta salekê, nizane hîn kulfetî çawa çêdike... çi
diqehre çi naqehre... çi dixwe çi naxwe.
 
Now for up to a year, she doesn't know how a family
functions... what makes them angry and what doesn't... what
they eat and what they don't.

177
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:30,000
Salekê şûnda nizane çi dibe. Dû re ew tişt namîne û bê av
didin serşiyayê xwedê...
 
After a year she doesn't know what happens. Then those
things don't remain, and they give water without waking up
by God...

178
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:37,000
Belê xaltîk, tu li ser zewacê diaxivî, te çend sal
zewicandî?
 
Yes auntie, you are talking about marriage, how many years
have you been married?

179
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:40,000
Bîst pênc... sîh sal e.
 
Twenty-five... thirty years.

180
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:43,000
Welleh yavrum, pêncî sal e...
 
By God my child, it's fifty years...

181
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:46,000
Dibe sîh sal û bîst pênc sal e.
 
It could be thirty years or twenty-five years.

182
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:54,000
Di wê jî... tifaqek heye. Vê heyatê bi hev re dewam dikin.
Noka ev tifaqo nemaye.
 
In that too... there is an agreement. They continue this
life together. Now this agreement is gone.

183
00:12:54,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Em kî nin, digot, medêketin ba hev... Serê xwe datanîn. Lê
noka dinêrin, noka tiştek wisa pê re tuneye.
 
Who are we, they used to say, coming together... They bowed
their heads. But now they look, now there is nothing like
that with them.

184
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
Berê serê xwe datanîn, noka danaynin...
 
Before they bowed their heads, now they don't...

185
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Berê ku ev kulfetî gşerrek ba, ku çibû, ba wan rast
nedibû... Wê serê xwe datanî.
 
Before, if the family had a fight, if something happened, it
wouldn't be fixed by them... She would bow her head.

186
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:17,000
Noka... wê qiseya xwe dikir, ew ê bavikê xwe yê mezin... Ew
diçû qiseya xwe ya dilê xwe dikir.
 
Now... she spoke her mind, her elder father... She would go
and speak the words of her heart.

187
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Noka min çi qise girt? Min xesiyê xwe jî, û apê xwe jî, û
kulfetê xwe jî. Me yane, ew jî helal bin. Me çi qewt kir.
 
Now what word did I take? I took my mother-in-law, and my
uncle-in-law, and my family. Meaning, may they be forgiven.
What did we endure.

188
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:32,000
Ez digotim ez xatirê Xwedê dikim... Siftê... û paşî xatirê
bavikê xwe, û sêyem xatirê bavikê xwe.
 
I would say I am doing it for the sake of God... Firstly...
and then for the sake of my father, and thirdly for the sake
of my father.

189
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:40,000
Meriv nabêje hema wisa ye. Min qîza te wisa got, ez qîza te
wisa got. Alhemdulillah.
 
One doesn't say it's just like that. "I told your daughter
this, I told your daughter that." Praise be to God.

190
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:42,000
Ê nexweş...
 
Well the sick...

191
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,000
Çi te got?
 
What did you say?

192
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:52,000
Ê dibên xwesiya berê hinekî dî erdnî bîka dikirin. Dibên
niha nawan in.
 
Well they say the mothers-in-law of the past used to be a
bit harsher on the brides. They say now they aren't like
that.

193
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:58,000
Welleh qurban, xwesiyên min ji min re... Xêr e, hezar rehme
lê bin...
 
By God my sacrifice, my mothers-in-law to me... They were
good, a thousand blessings upon them...

194
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:06,000
Ez jî yek ji wan, ew bûka mezin bûm, ji min re rind bû. Bes,
xeyrî me re, ê ku ez nizanim, xeyrî min jê re çawa kir.
 
I was one of them, I was that eldest bride, it was good for
me. But, other than us, the ones I don't know, other than
me, how they treated her.

195
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:15,000
Xeyrî min sê bûk hebûn. Ew xwedê dizanin. Di bûkên mezin de
ez bûm, êdî qîzên we mezin dibin, piçûk mezin dibin.
 
Besides me, there were three brides. God knows them. Among
the eldest brides was me, then your girls grew up, the
little ones grew up.

196
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:25,000
Berê, min xwestekek hebe bi wê re. Ew jî xwestekek bi min re
hebe. Em pê re dimeşiyan. Am pê re rûdiniştin.
 
In the past, I would have a wish with her. She would also
have a wish with me. We would walk with it. We would sit
with it.

197
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,000
Karê çolê jî wa...
 
The field work too, right...

198
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Na, em diçûn karê çolê jî. Paliya.
 
No, we would go to the field work too. To the harvest.

199
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,000
Paliya...
 
To the harvest...

200
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:37,000
Hewî malê, opînê malê... em gav û dew... Paliya qet tune.
 
Sweeping the house, cleaning the house... we didn't stop...
There was no break from the harvest.

201
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Nişkê derdikeve marê mezin, we nedît?
 
Suddenly a big snake would appear, didn't you see it?

202
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:45,000
Welle te nedîtiye, te qet nedîtiye, me jê nedît, tima me
nedîtiye... Çûna me de, di çolê de.
 
By God you haven't seen it, you have never seen it, we
didn't see it either, we constantly didn't see it... During
our time, in the fields.

203
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Lew hevalek... na giştî ne...
 
So a friend... no all of them...

204
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Kî diçûn... ew qasî, piçûk hebûn.
 
Who would go... there were that many, there were little
ones.

205
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,000
Ew zemanên we xweş bûn.
 
Those times of yours were beautiful.

206
00:14:54,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Wê rojnên xweş bûn, rûniştina xweş bû.
 
Those days were beautiful, the gatherings were beautiful.

207
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:05,000
Û kincên me bi destan, wekî tiştên te, kinc... Em kincên wa
bi destan dişuştin.
 
And our clothes were washed by hand, like your things,
clothes... We used to wash their clothes by hand.

208
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,000
We nan jî dikir.
 
You also made bread.

209
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:10,000
E wele, me nan jî dikir.
 
Oh yes, we made bread too.

210
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,000
Nanên... kî ji we re meq dida?
 
The breads... who used to press them for you?

211
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:18,000
Nan dikir... şîva xwe dikir. Û kincên xwe dişuştan. Û dîsa
berê malê, hemû paqijiya malê.
 
We made bread... made our dinner. And washed our clothes.
And again the front of the house, all the house cleaning.

212
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,000
Hîç berê te nedikir?
 
Did you never do it before?

213
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:22,000
Û dîsan... zeytûn hebû...
 
And again... there were olives...

214
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:25,000
Baran lê nedikir? Kola te... te dikir?
 
It didn't rain on them? Your digging... did you dig?

215
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:35,000
Ka me çi dikir? Eger nan bikim, şîvê bikim. Û kincên we
bişom. Ev e... min nanê te dikir, nanê xwe dikir.
 
Well what did we do? I would make bread, I would make
dinner. And I would wash your clothes. This is it... I made
your bread, I made my bread.

216
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,000
Yek xurce, yek xurce...
 
One sack, one sack...

217
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Sibehekê bar dikir, dikişand meqbesê.
 
One morning we loaded it, and hauled it to the press.

218
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:52,000
Qêçkê xwe yek dikir, wê xurcê yek, wê xurcê, bar dikir milê.
Diçû meqbesê... yek qemyonek... heta pêncî me da... yek
xemsîn me da.
 
We would gather our bags, one sack here, one sack there, and
carried it on our shoulders. We'd go to the press... a small
truck... we gave up to fifty... we gave one fifty-coin.

219
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:54,000
Kîlo.
 
Kilos.

220
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:58,000
Pêncî kîlo, em tavan ber dericê, li... siwar dikirin.
 
Fifty kilos, we put them by the stairs, and... loaded them.

221
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:15,000
Em hingî jî xort bûn, me zeytûn hûr dikir... zeyt min
derdixist. Hingî... min karê çolê dikir... min zeyt
derdixist. Min nan çêdikir. Min şîv dikir. Min kinc
dişuştin... Hemû karê malê dikişand.
 
We were young back then too, we crushed olives... I
extracted oil. Back then... I did the field work... I
extracted oil. I made bread. I made dinner. I washed
clothes... I carried the entire burden of the house.

222
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:18,000
Ê saetên we yên berê xweş bûn.
 
Well your old times were beautiful.

223
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:22,000
Welle, ewe tiştê berê, em nikanin rebetiya wê bikin.
 
By God, that is a thing of the past, we cannot match it
anymore.

224
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:26,000
Ê naha yavrum, nikanin rabitiyê bikin, bes çûye...
 
Well now my child, they cannot match it, it has just gone...

225
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:30,000
Eme naha vê rûniştinê nakin.
 
Now we don't even have these gatherings.

226
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:36,000
Xaltîk, sebirkirin... we ew qewet ji dilê me re bexş
dikirin.
 
Auntie, being patient... you bestowed that strength upon our
hearts.

227
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:50,000
Niha wisa nînin. Mehmezek... nizanin, noka qet nizanin.
Tiştên xwere di xwe de. Xwestiye xurt be.
 
Now they aren't like that. A spur... they don't know, now
they don't know at all. Things for themselves within
themselves. They wanted it to be strong.

228
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,000
Şelwelek dî nedigihîşt.
 
Another pair of trousers couldn't reach it.

229
00:16:53,000 --> 00:17:05,000
E wî şelek negiştin. E te şelek ne giştin, ewe qîzek çû. Kî
zane çi dibe...
 
Yes those trousers didn't reach. Yes your trousers didn't
reach, that was a girl going. Who knows what happens...

230
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Firîk bi destan çi dikirin? Firîk bi destan çêdikirin...
 
What did they do to the frikeh by hand? They made frikeh by
hand...

231
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,000
Eme fîrîk bi destan çêdikir.
 
We used to make frikeh by hand.

232
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Birxul jî bi destan çêdikirin?
 
Did you make bulgur by hand too?

233
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:18,000
Em birxul bi destan çêdikir, me dikeland. Em genim
dikelandin. Em dikelandin. Diqelandin... em tê danî bûn...
wê... em diçûn fîlan.
 
We made bulgur by hand, we boiled it. We boiled wheat. We
boiled it. Roasted it... we placed it in... that... we went
to things.

234
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:28,000
Berê xaltîk, dema ku baran nedihat, baran nedikirin, li
gundan, dema sersalê, ez dixwazim ji te bipirsim... hûn çawa
sersalê çêdikirin?
 
In the past auntie, when the rain didn't come, when it
didn't rain, in the villages, during the New Year, I want to
ask you... how did you celebrate the New Year?

235
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:48,000
Çawa sersal çêdikirin? Dema baran nedihatin, yanî me dît ku
nabe... ewan qeşmerek bi xwe çêdikirin. Gundî diçûn di
gundan de digeriyan. Jin û mêr... diçûn ber malan...
 
How did they celebrate the New Year? When the rains didn't
come, meaning we saw it wasn't happening... they would dress
up a fool. The villagers went and wandered around the
villages. Men and women... went to the houses...

236
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Yekî xwe qeşmer dikir, diçûn xaniyên gund. Kesên di hundur
de derdiketin hewşê... Bi avê li qeşmer dixistin. Qefik ji
wî re datanîn, wek bulxur, pere... zeytûn.
 
Someone would dress as the fool, they went to the houses of
the village. The people inside would come out to the
courtyard... They splashed water on the fool. They placed a
bowl for him, like bulgur, money... olives.

237
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:44,000
Dema wî gundî xelas dikirin, em dibêjin eger pere yan tişt
kom kiriban... kom dikirin û diçûn ber ziyaretan. Wê derê
xwarinek çêdikirin. Jina û mêran. Dua dikirin. Şev û roj
wisa dikirin. Her malên gund ji wan re tiştek didan, heta
baran dibarî.
 
When they finished that village, we say if they collected
money or items... they gathered them and went to the
shrines. There they cooked a meal. Women and men. They
prayed. They did this day and night. Every house in the
village gave them something, until it rained.

238
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:23,000
Ez pêşkêşvanê we bim... gîşkî min. Bes baran...
 
May I be your presenter... all of mine. Just the rain...

239
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:35,000
Eme... bûn, de kirin... heta kuçeyan meselen. Wekî xwedê,
weşlê... dikişîne we... mêr e jin in... e kiye...
 
We... were, well did it... up to the streets for example.
Like God, well... draws you... men and women... whoever it
is...

240
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:38,000
Çend sal in ku min baran ne dîtine.
 
It's been years since I've seen rain.

241
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:47,000
Maşellah xweş e. Xweşe maşellah, dibên mirovî, milletek...
zeviyên we... de te...
 
Mashallah it is beautiful. It's beautiful mashallah, they
say humanity, a nation... your fields... so you...

242
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:51,000
Kanê em ê niha... te bibînin. Kanî derketine wa...
 
Where will we now... see you. Where have they come out to...

243
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:55,000
Çawan me dîtine... çawan te... wî dîtine, me wisa dîtine.
 
How we have seen... how you... saw it, we have seen it like
that.

244
