00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:30,000
Erê, bera rez hebûn. Rez... yanî tirî... rez hebûn.
 
Yes, in the past there were vineyards. Vineyards... I mean
grapes... there were vineyards.

359
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:32,000
Tê bîra te ew kûmirê berê, tu ji min re behsa kûmir bikî?
 
Do you remember the charcoal of the past, can you talk to me
about the charcoal?

360
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:38,000
Kûmir, wek şabîk, darên şabîkê hebûn, mazî hebûn... em
diçûn, me dibir... me kom dikir...
 
Charcoal, like şabîk, there were şabîk trees, there were oak
trees... we went, we took it... we gathered it...

361
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:43,000
Heta tu... heta ew dibe kûmir... çawa? Heta dibe kûmir tu
darên wî bibî? ... xelk... kûmir difirotin?
 
Until you... until it becomes charcoal... how? Until it
becomes charcoal, you take its wood? ... people... sold
charcoal?

362
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:49,000
...ta ev dibe kom, me dikir jêr, e... me êgir berdidê, ew
derdiket, me ew difirot.
 
...until it becomes a pile, we put it down, uh... we set
fire to it, it came out, we sold it.

363
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:53,000
Ji bo firotinê bû? Ew dar, kîjan dar bûn ku we dikirin
kûmir?
 
Was it for selling? Those trees, which trees were they that
you made into charcoal?

364
00:28:53,000 --> 00:29:00,000
Darê mazî, û şabîk ... ew dar û darik... wek heye.. me ew
dar... wekî tewş ... dar tewş... me ew çêdikir...
 
The oak tree, and şabîk... those trees and sticks... as
there is.. we... those trees... like branches... tree
branches... we made it...

365
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:04,000
Û anha? Debara we.. ew tiştê kûmir... xilas bû. Jiyana we ya
anha çawa ye?
 
And now? Your livelihood... that charcoal thing... is
finished. How is your life now?

366
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:11,000
Piştî wê, wextê em derketin... min dît ew rezê ... zeytûn e
... me çandin ... zeytûn ...
 
After that, when we left... I saw those vineyards... it is
olives... we planted... olives...

367
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:14,000
Yanî gişkî dev ji kûmir berda, çûn ser çandiniya zeytûnan.
 
I mean everyone gave up on charcoal, they went into farming
olives.

368
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:17,000
Erê.. te dît. Ji bera me dest pê kiribû...
 
Yes.. you saw. From before we had started...

369
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:20,000
Her kesî zeytûn çandin... û çavdêrî...
 
Everyone planted olives... and care...

370
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:23,000
Her kesî cîyek girt û çand, ew...
 
Everyone took a place and planted, that...

371
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:28,000
Ez dikarim bibêjim ev gundê Tirmişa... wekî hemî dar in?
Yanî cîhê tû û mîşa... bû darê zeytûnê?
 
Can I say this village of Tirmişa... are they all trees? I
mean the place of berries and bees... became olive trees?

372
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:34,000
Cîhê kû re dît, hemû zeytûn ne. Tirmîşa û Mîşa, her cîh ...
her merivek... tije kirin e..
 
Wherever you saw a place, they are all olives. Tirmişa and
Mîşa, everywhere... every person... filled it..

373
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:40,000
Lê navê Tirmîşayê tu dizanî gundê Tirmîşa mebest jê çi ye?
Yanî çend Tirmîş hene di Tirmîşa de?
 
But the name Tirmişa do you know the village of Tirmişa what
is meant by it? I mean how many Tirmiş are there in Tirmişa?

374
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:45,000
Du Tirmîş hene, Tirmîşa Jor, Tirmîşa Jêrîn. Du heb in.
 
There are two Tirmiş, Upper Tirmişa, Lower Tirmişa. There
are two.

375
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:50,000
Ferqek ... cuda ... e... heye an tune? Gundê Tirmîşa mezin e
... an wek hev in?
 
Is there... a different... uh... difference or not? Is the
village of Tirmişa big... or are they the same?

376
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:56,000
Ferqek tine, e... cîh... yek e. Tirmîşa Jor... û Tirmîşa
Jêrîn e.
 
There is no difference, uh... the place... is one. Upper
Tirmişa... and Lower Tirmişa.

377
00:29:56,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Wê demê hemî... wekî gundên din.. deşt bûn..
 
At that time all of them... like other villages.. were
plains..

378
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Derheqê gund avakirinê ez dixwazim hinek agahiyan bidî min.
 
Plains... the plains are all one.

379
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,000
Derheqê gund avakirinê ez dixwazim hinek agahiyan bidî min.
 
Regarding the building of the village, I want you to give me
some information.

380
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:06,000
Erê, Fatkulakî ne. Fatkulakî ne.
 
Yes, they are the Fatkulakis. They are the Fatkulakis.

381
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:10,000
Cîranê me di ser Dêwatan, em ji Cizîra Botan in.
 
Our neighbors up in Dewatan, we are from Cizira Botan.

382
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:15,000
Gund ava kirine Fatkulakî ne.
 
The ones who built the village are the Fatkulakis.

383
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:20,000
Di ser sê rovan re gund, Fatkulakî ne.
 
Over three days the village, they are the Fatkulakis.

384
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:24,000
Naha bavê ciwan, ez dixwazim agahiyan bidî min.
 
Now, father of the young man, I want you to give me
information.

385
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:27,000
Ev gund dîroka wê çiqas sal e ketiye?
 
How many years of history does this village have?

386
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:32,000
Yanî ez dibêjim teqrîben... teqrîben çiqas sal e?
 
I mean, I say roughly... roughly how many years?

387
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:35,000
Bi rastî, ez pir bi van tiştan nizanm.
 
Honestly, I don't know much about these things.

388
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:39,000
Lê teqrîben ez dibêjim nêzîkî ser çar sed salî re ye.
 
But roughly I'd say it's close to over four hundred years.

389
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:40,000
Kevn e?
 
Is it old?

390
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:41,000
Erê, kevn e.
 
Yes, it is old.

391
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:43,000
Derûdor şikeft e.
 
The surroundings are caves.

392
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:48,000
Şikeft li dora me hene. Der hene.
 
There are caves around us. There are valleys.

393
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:51,000
Van şikeftan, berê... xwedanên malan tê de diman?
 
In the past... did the homeowners live in these caves?

394
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,000
Çima na.
 
Why not.

395
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:54,000
Piştî wê, xanî girtin?
 
After that, they built houses?

396
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:56,000
Paşê, eh, berdan, ha.
 
Later, uh, they left them, yes.

397
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:57,000
Paşê ava kirin.
 
Then they built them.

398
00:30:57,000 --> 00:31:00,000
Tabî wexta... qehm hene, şikeft hene...
 
Of course back then... there are clans, there are caves...

399
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:02,000
Tirasê me heye.
 
We have terraces.

400
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:03,000
Gundekî pir kevin e, û xweş e.
 
It's a very old village, and it's beautiful.

401
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:06,000
Di nav de xirabe li vir hene, ew dertên...
 
There are ruins inside here, they come out...

402
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:10,000
Mesela... sarnîcên kevin dertên. Sarnîcên hazir... kûpên avê
dertên.
 
For example... old cisterns are found. Ready cisterns...
water jugs are found.

403
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:13,000
Kûp... kûpên hazir wek mezin dertên.
 
Jugs... big ready-made jugs are found.

404
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:22,000
Ev di... xerbî gund, tirtube hene, tirbe... tirbe jî ji
kuferan dertên.
 
To the... west of the village, there are tombs... tombs...
tombs of infidels are found.

405
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:26,000
Bavê ciwan, kesên li vir dijîn îtîmadî xwe... liser ziraetê
dikin?
 
Father of the young man, do the people living here rely on
agriculture?

406
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:29,000
Maşallah behîv pir in em dibînin...
 
Mashallah, we see there are a lot of almonds...

407
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:31,000
Û zeytûnên we jî pir in.
 
And you have a lot of olives too.

408
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:35,000
Zeytûn pir in. Zeytûn ji deştê zêdetir in.
 
The olives are plenty. Olives are more than in the plains.

409
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:37,000
Bes axa me sivik e.
 
But our soil is light.

410
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:40,000
Axa me sivik e yanî. Samedê xazê ye.
 
Our soil is light, I mean. Because of the gas.

411
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:44,000
Wexta diçîne... dibe... wexta baran hebe dibe. Nabe.
 
When you plant... it grows... when there is rain, it grows.
Otherwise, it doesn't.

412
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:49,000
Piştî em dibêjin wek heyşt sal... naha em dibînin ku baran
pir hat. Ma we hilkêş kir?
 
After we say like eight years... now we see that a lot of
rain came. Did you plow?

413
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:52,000
Erê, erê. Îsal maşallah baran xweş e.
 
Yes, yes. This year mashallah the rain is good.

414
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:55,000
Bes mazerîk... yanî samedê xazê...
 
But still... I mean because of the gas...

415
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:59,000
Çepê çiyayî dore, axa wê çima zeîf e, na kûr e?
 
It's surrounded by mountains, why is its soil weak, is it
not deep?

416
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:01,000
Ne kûr e, axa wê ne kûr e.
 
It's not deep, its soil is not deep.

417
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,000
Ser taht e.
 
It's on rock.

418
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:04,000
Ne kûr e.
 
It's not deep.

419
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:11,000
Em darên wê dibînin çawa tên... te dît çawa samedê xazê...
 
We see how its trees grow... did you see how because of the
gas...

420
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:15,000
Bavê ciwan, naha di vî gundî de... eger em tiştekî li ser vî
gundî diyar bikin... mekteb heye li vî gundî?
 
Father of the young man, now in this village... if we point
out something about this village... is there a school in
this village?

421
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:18,000
Mekteb heye, camiya me xirab e... naha camiya xwe asîs
girtine...
 
There is a school, our mosque is ruined... now they have
laid the foundation for the mosque...

422
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:26,000
Dê çêkin înşallah. Em bi hêviya xwedê ne, camiya me
elhemdulîllah. Di nav destan de ye... dê bibe.
 
They will build it, God willing. We hope in God, our mosque,
thank God. It's in progress... it will be done.

423
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:27,000
Û mistewsif di vî gundî de tine?
 
And is there no clinic in this village?

424
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,000
Tine, na.
 
There isn't, no.

425
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:29,000
Seydelîye?
 
A pharmacy?

426
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:30,000
Tine.
 
There isn't.

427
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:32,000
Kesê ku nexweş dikeve, li vî gundî nexweş keve... dibin kû
derê?
 
A person who gets sick, falls sick in this village... where
do they take them?

428
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:34,000
Dibin Efrînê.
 
They take them to Afrin.

429
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:35,000
Efrîn...
 
Afrin...

430
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:37,000
Êdî em dibin Efrînê. Em dibin Efrînê, cihekî din tine ye.
 
We just take them to Afrin. We take them to Afrin, there is
nowhere else.

431
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:39,000
Bes dar û Efrîn.
 
Just trees and Afrin.

432
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:41,000
Gund... navçeya Şiyê ye?
 
The village... is in the sub-district of Shiye?

433
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:43,000
Hmm, navçeya Şiyê ye.
 
Hmm, it's the sub-district of Shiye.

434
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:45,000
Çiqas kîlometre ji navçeya Şiyê dûr e?
 
How many kilometers is it away from the Shiye sub-district?

435
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:49,000
Ji Şiyê we teqrîben... şeş heft kîlometro dûr e.
 
From your Shiye roughly... it's six or seven kilometers
away.

436
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:51,000
Nêzîk e, ne pir dûr e.
 
It's close, not very far.

437
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:54,000
Û gundên cîranê gundê we... em dibînin Hesen...
 
And the neighboring villages to your village... we see
Hesen...

438
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:56,000
Şikeftko ye.
 
There is Shikeftko.

439
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:57,000
Hesenkelo, Şikeftko...
 
Hesenkelo, Shikeftko...

440
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:58,000
Mehsereya tê...
 
Mehsereya comes...

441
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:00,000
Birko tê, Raco tê, Hac Qaso tê...
 
Birko comes, Raco comes, Hac Qaso comes...

442
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:02,000
Cema dajo tê, gundê Hesen tê...
 
Cema dajo comes, the village of Hesen comes...

443
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:09,000
Hodo tê, Erendê tê... Şiyê tê, Çeqela tê... Mistikê tê...
Qermîliq tê. Dora me wisa ne.
 
Hodo comes, Erende comes... Shiye comes, Cheqela comes...
Mistike comes... Qermiliq comes. Our surroundings are like
that.

444
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,000
El gundê bilind e, Tirmîşa?
 
Is the village high up, Tirmisha?

445
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:13,000
Ê hemû ji van gundan bilind in. Gundê Tirmîşa ye.
 
It's higher than all these villages. It's the village of
Tirmisha.

446
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:16,000
Gundê Tirmîşa... bi rastî gundekî pir xweş e, em pir kêfxweş
bûn bi dîtina we.
 
The village of Tirmisha... it's truly a very beautiful
village, we were very happy to see you.

447
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:19,000
Em jî pir kêf, pir kêfxweş bûn ku we ev der dît.
 
We are also very happy, very happy that you saw this place.

448
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:22,000
Em dixwazin, tebîeta... tebîeta navçeya Şiyê, tebîeta Efrînê
xweş e. Em pê kêfxweş bûn...
 
We want, the nature... the nature of Shiye sub-district, the
nature of Afrin is beautiful. We were happy with it...

449
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:30,000
Welleh xweş e... welleh xweş e... înşallah... aşiqê li vî
menzereyî dibin... deşt e we û deşt e me. Xwedê we biparêze.
Xwedê karê we pêş de bibe.
 
By God it's beautiful... by God it's beautiful... God
willing... they fall in love with this scenery... it's your
plain and our plain. May God protect you. May God advance
your work.

450
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:32,000
Em pir kêfxweş bûn, înşallah...
 
We were very happy, God willing...

451
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:34,000
Ji ber ku wextê me... nêzîk e diqede.
 
Because our time... is almost up.

452
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:39,000
Van tiştan, em pê kêfxweş in... navê we, em xwe pê kêfxweş
in, em dixwazin... em jî dixwazin hemşeherên xwe şa bikin.
 
These things, we are happy with them... your name, we are
happy with it, we want... we also want to make our fellow
citizens happy.

453
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:40,000
Xweş e.
 
It's nice.

454
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:41,000
Ji ber ku wextê me bi elam e...
 
Because our time is limited...

455
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:46,000
Ciyê Efrînê... çi gund hebe em dixwazin... em jî nîşan
bidin, em zanibin Efrîn kevn e... navê me li ser malperan
hebe...
 
Places of Afrin... whatever village there is we want to...
we also want to show it, so we know Afrin is old... so our
name is on the websites...

456
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:48,000
Ev e.
 
That is it.

457
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

458
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:51,000
Em pir kêfxweş in, Bavê Ciwan.
 
We are very happy, Father of the young man.

459
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:55,000
Em jê pir kêfxweş in... û Xwedê jê razî be... û saetên we
xweş bin...
 
We are very happy with it... and may God be pleased with
it... and have a good time...

460
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,000
Ser serê me, Bavê Ciwan.
 
You're very welcome, Father of the young man.

461
00:33:56,000 --> 00:34:02,000
Em sipasiya we dikin, em sipasiya gundê Tirmîşa tevahî
dikin.
 
We thank you, we thank the entire village of Tirmisha.

462
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:03,000
Qusûra me nebin...
 
Please excuse our shortcomings...

463
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:12,000
Bernameyek wisa... em pir westiyayî bûn, me meqsedek xweş
dît... me ew pêşkêş kir... em tiştekî din nakin. Em wisa
rûniştin. Xwedê rehma xwe li we bike.
 
Such a program... we were very tired, we found a nice
spot... we presented it... we aren't doing anything else. We
just sat like this. May God have mercy on you.

464
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:18,000
Hûn jî di wextê xwe de hatin... êdî em jî wextê we
nagirin... welle, welle...
 
You also came at your time... so we won't take up your
time... by God, by God...

465
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:22,000
Pir kêfxweş bûn, tu emrek, daxwazeke te heye, tu bixwazî
bibêjî?
 
We were very happy, do you have any order, any request,
anything you want to say?

466
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:23,000
Na welle... tiştek dî na... xwedê we biparêze.
 
No by God... nothing else... may God protect you.

467
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:24,000
Xwedê ji te razî be.
 
May God be pleased with you.

468
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:25,000
Xwedê ji te razî be.
 
May God be pleased with you.

469
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:26,000
Ser çavan.
 
You are welcome.

470
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:27,000
Ser çavê min...
 
You are very welcome...

471
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:47,000
(Music)
 
(Music)

472
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:55,000
Belê temaşevanan... naha em hatin derbasî... gundê Tirmîşa
bûn. Û gundê Tirmîşa jî em derbasî malekê bûn.
 
Yes viewers... now we have entered... the village of
Tirmisha. And in the village of Tirmisha we entered a house.

473
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:59,000
Vê malê wekî hûn dibînin, avahiya wê kevn e, û wek qeleya
mezin xuya dike.
 
As you can see this house, its building is old, and it looks
like a large castle.

474
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:03,000
Û hûn vê sahnê dibînin û ev der... em tê de xwarinê
dixwin...
 
And you see this scene and this place... we are eating in
it...

475
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:07,000
Vê xwarina me, yanî ev tişt naha em di wê malê de dibînin,
ev bereket e...
 
This food of ours, I mean these things we see now in this
house, this is a blessing...

476
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:11,000
Û em pir kêfxweş in... ku ev gund... wisa ev tiştan hifz
kirine.
 
And we are very happy... that this village... has preserved
these things like this.

477
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:17,000
Belkî em herin... wekî wêneyên me li ser facebookê dît...
min eciband.
 
Maybe we will go... as we saw the pictures on Facebook... I
liked it.

478
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,000
Em pir kêfxweş in.
 
We are very happy.

479
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:26,000
Înşallah... cihek din... eger em mecalekê bibînin, em ê
biçin. Li gundê Tirmîşa em ê ji we re xeberekê bidin. Ka ev
mal çiqas sal in ava bûye...
 
God willing... another place... if we find an opportunity,
we will go. In the village of Tirmisha we will give you some
information. About how many years ago this house was
built...

480
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:33,000
Çiqas sal... ava kirin...
 
How many years... it was built...

481
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:37,000
Û wekî hûn dibînin, dîmeneke pir xweş e zarok bi hev re, ev
tişt...
 
And as you can see, it's a very beautiful scene the children
together, these things...

482
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:40,000
Di her malekê de heye.
 
It's in every house.

483
00:36:40,000 --> 00:37:00,000
(Music)
 
(Music)

484
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,000
Apo, siba te bi xêr.
 
Uncle, good morning to you.

